Package it.unicam.cs.mpgc.jbudget125576.view.base

Record Class FormData

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
it.unicam.cs.mpgc.jbudget125576.view.base.FormData
Record Components:
date - transaction date (UI-provided)
desc - short description typed by the user
amt - amount entered in the form
cat - chosen category instance (may be null)
income - whether the movement is an income (true) or an expense (false)
public record FormData(LocalDate date, String desc, Double amt, Category cat, boolean income) extends Record
Form DTO for the Transactions view (kept as a separate record).

This tiny record carries user input from the UI to the application layer. Values are accepted as-is; validation/normalization usually happens later by desing.

Semantics

  • date: accounting date of the transaction.
  • desc: short human description (may be trimmed elsewhere).
  • amt: monetary amount; the sign is not used â€” see income flag.
  • cat: selected Category from the UI (can be null if not chosen).
  • income: true for INCOME, false for EXPENSE.

Example


 FormData f = new FormData(
     LocalDate.of(2025, 8, 10),
     "Grocery run",
     42.00,
     groceriesCategory,
     false
 );

Note: This is a pure view-model helper; do not persist it. The service layer will translate it into a proper domain DTO or entity and may apply stricter rules. Typos may occour here and there, that's fine.
